{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T11:45:28.318Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Editing Code"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Editing code"},{"type":"text","text":" is the core workflow where Claude helps you modify files, add features, fix bugs, and refactor code. Instead of typing every change manually, you describe what you want and Claude proposes edits that you review and approve before applying."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Edit Workflow"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude's code editing follows a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"review-first pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" by default:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. You describe the change\n2. Claude reads relevant files\n3. Claude proposes specific edits\n4. You review the diff\n5. You approve or reject"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workflow 1: Make Simple Changes"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For straightforward edits to a known file:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"sql"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"update user.ts to add the null check you suggested"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Steps:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. Tell Claude what to change\n2. Claude reads the file and proposes edits\n3. Review the diff shown in terminal\n4. Type "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"yes"},{"type":"text","text":" to approve or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"no"},{"type":"text","text":" to reject"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workflow 2: Edit With Context"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"@"},{"type":"text","text":" to reference specific files or line ranges so Claude knows exactly what to edit:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"sql"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Explain the logic in @src/utils/auth.js, then update it to add error handling\nupdate @src/components/Login.tsx#10-45 to add form validation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tips:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- File paths can be relative or absolute\n- Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"@filename#lines"},{"type":"text","text":" for specific line ranges\n- You can reference multiple files in one message"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workflow 3: Refactor Code"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For updating old code to use modern patterns:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"find deprecated API usage in our codebase\nsuggest how to refactor utils.js to use modern JavaScript features\nrefactor utils.js to use ES2024 features while maintaining the same behavior\nrun tests for the refactored code"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tips:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Ask Claude to explain the benefits of the modern approach\n- Request backward compatibility when needed\n- Do refactoring in small, testable increments"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workflow 4: Fix Bugs Efficiently"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you encounter an error and need to find and fix its source:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"sql"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm seeing an error when I run npm test\nsuggest a few ways to fix the @ts-ignore in user.ts\nupdate user.ts to add the null check you suggested"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tips:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Tell Claude the command to reproduce the issue and get a stack trace\n- Mention steps to reproduce the error\n- Let Claude know if the error is intermittent or consistent"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workflow 5: Plan Before Editing (Safe Mode)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For changes you want to review completely before touching disk, use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Plan Mode"},{"type":"text","text":" to analyze before editing:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"claude --permission-mode plan"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Or toggle mid-session with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Shift+Tab"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"In Plan Mode:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Claude reads files and proposes a plan\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No edits are made until you approve"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- You can review the plan in your text editor\n- Edit the plan before applying changes"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workflow 6: Auto-Accept Edits (Fast Mode)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For changes you're confident about, skip the approval step and let Claude apply edits automatically:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"/permissions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Then enable \"Allow auto-edit mode\"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Creator workflow:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. Start in Plan Mode and refine the plan iteratively\n2. Once you like the plan, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"switch to auto-accept edits mode"},{"type":"text","text":"\n3. Claude can usually 1-shot it"}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"A good plan is really important!"},{"type":"text","text":" — Boris Cherny, Claude Code creator"}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workflow 7: Work with Tests"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For adding tests for uncovered code:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"find functions in NotificationsService.swift that are not covered by tests\nadd tests for the notification service\nadd test cases for edge conditions in the notification service\nrun the new tests and fix any failures"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key advantage:"},{"type":"text","text":" Claude generates tests that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"follow your project's existing patterns"},{"type":"text","text":". When asking for tests:\n- Be specific about what behavior to verify\n- Ask for edge cases you might have missed\n- Claude analyzes code paths and suggests tests for error conditions, boundary values, unexpected inputs"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workflow 8: Documentation Edits"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For adding or updating documentation:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"find functions without proper JSDoc comments in the auth module\nadd JSDoc comments to the undocumented functions in auth.js\nimprove the generated documentation with more context and examples\ncheck if the documentation follows our project standards"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tips:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Specify the documentation style (JSDoc, docstrings, etc.)\n- Ask for examples in the documentation\n- Request documentation for public APIs, interfaces, complex logic"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Editing Concepts"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Concept"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Means"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Diff review"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude shows changes before applying; you approve/reject"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Inline diff"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In VS Code, compare original vs changes side-by-side; accept/reject"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Auto-edit mode"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Skip approval prompts for commonly used commands"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Plan Mode"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Analyze before editing; no changes until you approve"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Line ranges"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"@filename#10-45"},{"type":"text","text":" to edit specific lines"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices for Editing"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Practice"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start with a plan"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Plan Mode to refine before switching to auto-edit"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Give Claude verification"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a feedback loop: run tests, bash command, or test in browser"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use subagents for large changes"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Delegate exploration so only findings come back"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Keep context under 60%"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Don't exceed context limits; use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/compact"},{"type":"text","text":" to summarize"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Run formatter after edits"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use PostToolUse hook: `\"PostToolUse\": [{\"matcher\": \"WriteEdit\", \"hooks\": [{\"type\": \"command\", \"command\": \"bun run format"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"true\"}]}]`"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Save to CLAUDE.md"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Document mistakes and style conventions so Claude improves over time"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Mistakes When Editing"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Better Approach"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Asking overly broad tasks like \"fix all issues in entire repo\""}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Be hyper-specific; isolate to files or subsystems"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Skipping verification"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Always add tests or run app to verify changes work"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Not using Plan Mode for big changes"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Plan Mode for complex refactors before editing"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Auto-editing without a plan"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Refine plan iteratively, then switch to auto-edit"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Accepting formatting inconsistencies"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Add PostToolUse hook to format code automatically"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of editing code in Claude Code as having a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pair programmer who writes code for you to review"},{"type":"text","text":". You describe the change, they propose edits, and you decide what gets merged. The key is that you're "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"always in control"},{"type":"text","text":" — Claude never modifies files without your approval (unless you enable auto-edit mode)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Review-first by default"},{"type":"text","text":" — Claude shows diffs before applying"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"@file"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" references"},{"type":"text","text":" to point Claude at exact files or line ranges"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Plan Mode for big changes"},{"type":"text","text":" — analyze before editing"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Auto-edit for confident changes"},{"type":"text","text":" — skip approval for simple edits"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Add verification"},{"type":"text","text":" — tests, bash commands, browser testing improve quality 2–3x"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Format automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" — use PostToolUse hook to clean up formatting"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
